claim.claim-text:
A magnet evaluating device, characterized by comprising:
an excitation coil that generates a magnetic field of a magnitude within a range corresponding to a region including an insulating material between at least one magnetic section of a magnet, which is formed by connecting a plurality of magnetic sections with insulating material in between, and another magnetic section that is adjacent to the one magnetic section;
a detection coil that detects an eddy current occurring in the magnet;
a transfer unit that transfers an evaluation magnet, which is made by connecting a plurality of magnetic sections with insulating material in between, and a master magnet, which is made by connecting a plurality of magnetic sections with insulating material in between, through the magnetic field; and
an evaluation unit that compares a measured value, measuring a voltage or a current that is generated in the detection coil when the evaluation magnet passes through the magnetic field, with a measured value, measuring the voltage or the current that is generated in the detection coil when the master magnet passes through the magnetic field.
